Property.Name: Palette
Property.Desc: Palette for chart. If "None", PaletteCustomColors is used.

Property.Name: PaletteCustomColors
Property.Desc: Custom palette. Choose from options or type in your own colors. Option 1 is Dyn365 default, Option 2 is the Power BI color scheme.

Property.Name: MarkerBorderColor
Property.Desc: The border color of the marker.

Property.Name: MarkerBorderWidth
Property.Desc: The border width of the marker.

Property.Name: MarkerColor
Property.Desc: The marker color.

Property.Name: MarkerSize
Property.Desc: The size of the marker.

Property.Name: MarkerStep
Property.Desc: An integer value that determines how often to display data point markers. The default value is one (1).

Property.Name: MarkerStyle
Property.Desc: Sets the marker style.

Property.Name: Enabled
Property.Desc: Series is enabled by default. If set to "False" the series will not be visible on the chart.

Property.Name: Palette
Property.Desc: Using a palette will color each items of the series differently. Only system palettes can be used on a series.

Property.Name: ShadowOffset
Property.Desc: To implement shadowing, use a value other than zero (0). A positive value will result in a shadow that shifts down and to the right. A negative value will result in a shadow that shifts up and to the left.

Property.Name: ShadowColor
Property.Desc: Gets or sets the shadow color of a series, which can be to any valid ARGB (alpha, red, green, blue) value. The alpha value can be used to achieve a realistic shadow effect; try using a color value of "128,0,0,0" for shadows.

Property.Name: BorderDashStyle
Property.Desc: DashStyle of border. Only applied if BorderWidth is 1 or higher.

Property.Name: BorderColor
Property.Desc: Color of border. Only applied if BorderWidth is 1 or higher.

Property.Name: BorderWidth
Property.Desc: Width of border in pixels. When used, also set BorderColor and BorderDashStyle. Also used for increasing width of line charts.

Property.Name: LabelForeColor
Property.Desc: Color for the label text inside the chart if shown.

Property.Name: LabelFormat
Property.Desc: Use to change values to display in thousands/millions etc. Type your label format or select a preset option from the list. Or select from list and make changes as needed.

Property.Name: Label
Property.Desc: Label for this series. Overridden if IsValueShownAsLabel="True". Commonly supported keywords; #AXISLABEL, #PERCENT, #MIN, #MAX, #TOTAL, #FIRST, #LAST. Formatting of keyword values are not supported.

Property.Name: IsValueShownAsLabel
Property.Desc: If "True", the value of the series is shown as the label. Format of number can be set in "LabelFormat". If "False" set the label in the "Label" property.

Property.Name: Font
Property.Desc: Font type and size for the label text inside the chart if shown.

Property.Name: YAxisType
Property.Desc: Is the series on the Primary or Secondary axis? If empty, series will be on the Primary axis by default.

Property.Name: Color
Property.Desc: The color for this individual series. If empty, color palette will be used.

Property.Name: LegendText
Property.Desc: Text to be shown in the legend for this series.

Property.Name: IsVisibleInLegend
Property.Desc: Set to false to remove item from appearing in the legend.

Property.Desc: Value from 0-99. Default 60. The larger the value of DoughnutRadius, the smaller the hole of the chart. If set to 99, the doughnut hole looks very small and looks like a Pie chart.

Property.Desc: Drawing style of the pie or doughnut.

Property.Name: CalloutLineColor
Property.Desc: The line color of the callout for the labels of Funnel and Pyramid charts.

Property.Name: FunnelInsideLabelAlignment
Property.Desc: Placement of label inside the funnel. Only applies if FunnelLabelStyle is set to "Inside"

Property.Name: FunnelOutsideLabelPlacement
Property.Desc: Placement of the data label outside the Funnel chart. Only applies FunnelLabelStyle = Outside or OutsideInColumn.

Property.Name: FunnelLabelStyle
Property.Desc: Sets the placement of the data label.

Property.Name: FunnelMinPointHeight
Property.Desc: Minimum height of a data point in the Funnel chart, measured in relative coordinates. Value range 0-100, default 0. Specifying a value eliminates very thin slices.

Property.Name: FunnelPointGap
Property.Desc: The gap size between the points of a Funnel chart, measured in relative coordinates. Value range 0-100. Default 0.

Property.Name: FunnelNeckHeight
Property.Desc: The neck height of the Funnel chart as a percentage of the chart. Value range 0-100. Default 5. Only applies if FunnelStyle="YIsHeight"

Property.Name: FunnelNeckWidth
Property.Desc: The neck width of the Funnel chart as a percentage of the chart. Value range 0-100. Default 5. Only applies if FunnelStyle="YIsWidth"

Property.Name: FunnelStyle
Property.Desc: Defines if the value is represented by the heigth of each area, or by the width.Default = YIsHeight

Property.Name: PixelPointGapDepth
Property.Desc: 3D charts only. Specifies the 3D gap depth in pixels.

Property.Name: EmptyPointValue
Property.Desc: If a value of Average is used, the chart is drawn as though a point exists, and has a value of the average of the two adjacent points. If Zero is used, the chart is drawn as though a point exists with a zero value.

Property.Name: BubbleScaleMax
Property.Desc: Recommended to leave as empty or "Auto". Specifies the Y value that is represented by the maximum bubble size, which is set by BubbleMaxSize.

Property.Name: BubbleScaleMin
Property.Desc: Recommended to leave as empty or "Auto". Specifies the Y value that is represented by the maximum bubble size, which is set by BubbleMinSize.

Property.Name: BubbleMaxSize
Property.Desc: Specifies the maximum size of the bubble radius as a percentage of the chart area size. Default is 15

Property.Name: BubbleMinSize
Property.Desc: Specifies the minimum size of the bubble radius as a percentage of the chart area size. Default is 3

Property.Name: BubbleUseSizeForLabel
Property.Desc: Specifies whether to use the bubble size as the data point label.

Property.Name: LabelStyle
Property.Desc: Specifies the label position of the data point.

Property.Name: BackColor
Property.Desc: Sets the background color of the chart area.

Property.Name: BackGradientStyle
Property.Desc: Sets the orientation for the background gradient of a chart area, and also determines whether or not a gradient is used.

Property.Name: BackSecondaryColor
Property.Desc: Sets the secondary color for the background of the chart area.

Property.Name: BackHatchStyle
Property.Desc: Sets the HatchStyle for the background.

Property.Name: BorderWidth
Property.Desc: The width of the border measured in pixels.

Property.Name: BorderColor
Property.Desc: The color of the border line. Only applies if BorderWidth is 1 or higher.

Property.Name: BorderDashStyle
Property.Desc: The dash style of the border. Only applies if BorderWidth is 1 or higher.

Property.Name: Visible
Property.Desc: Toggles visibility of the chart area. Effective hides the entire chart. Probably good idea to not change this one.

Property.Name: ArrowStyle
Property.Desc: Sets the arrow style of a two-dimensional (2D) axis; this style is not applied to three-dimensional (3D) chart areas.

Property.Name: Crossing
Property.Desc: Sets the value at which an axis is crossed by its associated axis. I.e. can change the center point of the axis and bars/columns can move in either direction. Consider setting IsMarksNextToAxis to "False" if used.

Property.Name: Enabled
Property.Desc: Enabled by default. If "False", the axis and title is removed entirely, but bars/columns and series will remain.

Property.Name: InterlacedColor
Property.Desc: Sets the color of interlaced strip lines. Colors the interval between the major gridlines. Only applies if IsInterlaced="True"

Property.Name: Interval
Property.Desc: Sets the interval of an axis. The Interval property of a major tick mark, grid line or label of the axis has priority over the Interval property setting of the Axis object.

Property.Name: IntervalAutoMode
Property.Desc: Determines if a fixed number of intervals is used on the axis, or if the number of intervals depends on the axis size.

Property.Name: IntervalOffset
Property.Desc: Sets the interval offset of an axis. I.e. the value 100 would mean the labels on the axis start at the value 100.

Property.Name: IsInterlaced
Property.Desc: Determines if interlaced strip lines are displayed for an axis.

Property.Name: IsLabelAutoFit
Property.Desc: Determines whether axis labels are automatically fitted.

Property.Name: IsLogarithmic
Property.Desc: Indicates whether the axis is logarithmic. Zeros or negative data values are not allowed on logarithmic charts. Optionally use LogarithmBase in conjunction with this property.

Property.Name: IsMarginVisible
Property.Desc: Determines whether an axis margin will be used.

Property.Name: IsMarksNextToAxis
Property.Desc: Determines whether tick marks and axis labels move with an axis if the crossing point of an axis changes. Set to "False" if crossing is used or chart includes both positive and negative values.

Property.Name: IsReversed
Property.Desc: Reverses the orientation of the axis.

Property.Name: IsStartedFromZero
Property.Desc: Use to highligth subtle differences in datasets that have large amounts. Indicates if the minimum value of the axis will be automatically set to zero if all data point values are positive. If there are negative data point values, the minimum value of the data points will be used.

Property.Name: LabelAutoFitMaxFontSize
Property.Desc: The maximum font size that can be used by the label auto-fitting algorithm.

Property.Name: LabelAutoFitMinFontSize
Property.Desc: The minimum font size that can be used by the label auto-fitting algorithm.

Property.Name: LabelAutoFitStyle
Property.Desc: Sets the allowable label changes that can be made to enable the label to be fit along an axis.

Property.Name: LineColor
Property.Desc: Sets the line color of the axis.

Property.Name: LineDashStyle
Property.Desc: Sets the dash style of the line of the axis.

Property.Name: LineWidth
Property.Desc: The width of the axis in pixels.

Property.Name: LogarithmBase
Property.Desc: Value that represents the logarithm base value for the logarithmic axis. The default value is base 10.

Property.Name: Maximum
Property.Desc: Sets the maximum value of an axis. I.e. if charting a scale that goes from 0-100, set the max to 100 to avoid the chart being longer than the actual values.

Property.Name: Minimum
Property.Desc: Sets the minimum value of an axis.

Property.Name: MaximumAutoSize
Property.Desc: Sets the maximum size of the axis, measured as a percentage of the chart area. This value is used by the automatic layout algorithm.

Property.Name: Title
Property.Desc: Sets the title of the axis.

Property.Name: TitleAlignment
Property.Desc: Sets the alignment of an axis title.

Property.Name: TitleFont
Property.Desc: Sets the title font properties of an axis.

Property.Name: TitleForeColor
Property.Desc: Sets the text color of an axis title.

Property.Name: ToolTip
Property.Desc: Sets the tooltip used for the axis.

Property.Name: Angle
Property.Desc: Sets a value that represents the angle at which the font is drawn.

Property.Desc: Sets a flag that indicates whether the label is enabled.

Property.Name: Font
Property.Desc: Sets the font of the label.

Property.Name: ForeColor
Property.Desc: Sets the color of the label.

Property.Name: Format
Property.Desc: Sets the format. Used for values. Select from the list to show values in the thousands or millions, or type a custom format to use.

Property.Desc: Sets the value of the label interval. Only for the labels. The interval for the grid is defined on the axis directly.

Property.Name: IntervalOffset

Property.Desc: Sets the unit of measurement of the label interval offset. Intended for dates, but Dynamics 365 haven't rendered this properly since Dynamics CRM 2011.

Property.Name: IntervalType
Property.Desc: Sets the unit of measurement of the label interval. Intended for dates, but Dynamics 365 haven't rendered this properly since Dynamics CRM 2011.

Property.Desc: Determines whether the labels are shown at axis ends.

Property.Name: IsStaggered
Property.Desc: Determines whether the labels are shown with an offset.

Property.Name: LineColor
Property.Desc: The color of the grid line.

Property.Name: LineDashStyle
Property.Desc: The dash style of the grid line.

Property.Name: LineWidth
Property.Desc: The width of the grid line in pixels.

Property.Name: Size
Property.Desc: Sets the length of tick marks. The length is measured in units that represent a percentage of the height or width of the chart image, depending on the axis. Default value is 1.0 percent.

Property.Name: TickMarkStyle
Property.Desc: Sets the tick mark style. Default value is "OutsideArea".

Property.Name: BreakLineStyle
Property.Desc: The style of the break line that will be used to draw the scale break.

Property.Name: CollapsibleSpaceThreshold
Property.Desc: The CollapsibleSpaceThreshold property is a percentage of the Y axis. The default value for 25 means that the data in your series must have a difference of at least 25% for the ScaleBreak to appear. Value range 10-90, Default ="25"

Property.Name: Enabled
Property.Desc: Is the ScaleBreak enabled. Must be set to "True" for other scale break properties to take effect.

Property.Name: LineColor
Property.Desc: The color of the scale break line.

Property.Name: LineDashStyle
Property.Desc: The dash style of the scale break line.

Property.Name: LineWidth
Property.Desc: The width of hte scale break line.

Property.Name: MaxNumberOfBreaks
Property.Desc: Max number of breaks supported. Value range 0-5, default ="2"

Property.Name: Spacing
Property.Desc: Value represent the gap of the break as percentage of the axis. Value range 0-10, default ="1.5" percent.

Property.Name: StartFromZero
Property.Desc: Defines if the chart should start looking for possible scale breaks from either zero, or from the lowest value in your data set. Default ="Auto"

Property.Name: ArrowStyle
Property.Desc: Sets the arrow style of a two-dimensional (2D) axis; this style is not applied to three-dimensional (3D) chart areas.

Property.Name: Crossing
Property.Desc: Sets the value at which an axis is crossed by its associated axis. I.e. can change the center point of the axis and bars/columns can move in either direction. Consider setting IsMarksNextToAxis to "False" if used.

Property.Name: Enabled
Property.Desc: Enabled by default. If "False", the axis and title is removed entirely, but bars/columns and series will remain.

Property.Name: InterlacedColor
Property.Desc: Sets the color of interlaced strip lines. Colors the interval between the major gridlines. Only applies if IsInterlaced="True"

Property.Name: Interval
Property.Desc: Sets the interval of an axis. The Interval property of a major tick mark, grid line or label of the axis has priority over the Interval property setting of the Axis object.

Property.Name: IntervalAutoMode
Property.Desc: Determines if a fixed number of intervals is used on the axis, or if the number of intervals depends on the axis size.

Property.Name: IntervalOffset
Property.Desc: Sets the interval offset of an axis. I.e. the value 100 would mean the labels on the axis start at the value 100.

Property.Name: IsInterlaced
Property.Desc: Determines if interlaced strip lines are displayed for an axis.

Property.Name: IsLabelAutoFit
Property.Desc: Determines whether axis labels are automatically fitted.

Property.Name: IsLogarithmic
Property.Desc: Indicates whether the axis is logarithmic. Zeros or negative data values are not allowed on logarithmic charts. Optionally use LogarithmBase in conjunction with this property.

Property.Name: IsMarginVisible
Property.Desc: Determines whether an axis margin will be used.

Property.Name: IsMarksNextToAxis
Property.Desc: Determines whether tick marks and axis labels move with an axis if the crossing point of an axis changes. Set to "False" if crossing is used or chart includes both positive and negative values.

Property.Name: IsReversed
Property.Desc: Reverses the orientation of the axis.

Property.Name: IsStartedFromZero
Property.Desc: Use to highligth subtle differences in datasets that have large amounts. Indicates if the minimum value of the axis will be automatically set to zero if all data point values are positive. If there are negative data point values, the minimum value of the data points will be used.

Property.Name: LabelAutoFitStyle
Property.Desc: Sets the allowable label changes that can be made to enable the label to be fit along an axis.

Property.Name: StartFromZero
